    <text>
        <body>
            
            <div1 type="letter">
                
                <pb facs="nei.j4a.10.18" />
                
                <fw type="curatorial">18</fw>
                
                <opener>
                    <dateline>
                        September
                        Twenty
                        1923
                    </dateline>
                    
                    <salute>Dear Mr. Neihardt:-</salute>
                </opener>
                <p>I am exceedingly glad to comply with the request of the committee having the dedication of our new stadium under way in asking you if you could write a few verses to be read on October 20th when the formal dedicatory exercises will be held. I realize that for an epic poet this may seem like a bit of hack work to you, but nevertheless it would be most highly appreciated by the community and if you feel that you can comply we shall be highly gratified.</p>
                
                <p>I am asking the committee to send you printed matter in regard to the stadium so that you can perhaps visualize it a little better. It is really an enormous affair, will be when completed architecturally beautiful and not unworthy of comparison with some of the historic structures erected by the Greeks and Romans. I think even in the palmiest days of the Empire such a building would have been considered well worth while in almost any of the provincial seats of government outside of a few metropolitan cities.</p>
                
                <p>In making this suggestion to you I hope you will not feel that I think Pegasus can be hooked up to a plow. The verses would be as many or as few as inspiration or the lack of it might determine. I do, however, want your name on the program so that the public may feel that your connection with the University is vital and not merely formal.</p>
                <closer>
                    <salute>Yours very truly,</salute>
                
                    <!--unsigned--> 
                </closer>
                
            </div1>
        </body>
        
